  "market_context": "Gold on the hourly chart displaced down and made a new low. The analyst adjusted the Fibonacci retracement on the new displacement leg, identifying an OTE zone that overlapped with an hourly fair value gap as a premium PD array for shorts.",
  "key_observation": "On the hourly OTE/FVG confluence, price reached the 0.79 level inside kill zone with body still respecting the hourly fair value gap, then displaced lower on the 5-minute, leaving a 5-minute FVG and a 1-minute order block for a precision short entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the gold hourly chart, identified displacement lower and applied the Fibonacci retracement to the displacement range to find the OTE zone.",
    "Step 2: Adjusted the Fib after price made a new low and located a PD array confluence — an hourly fair value gap inside the OTE.",
    "Step 3: Dropped down to the 5-minute timeframe and observed price generating equal lows (sellside liquidity) before reaching up toward the hourly OTE/FVG.",
    "Step 4: Filtered out the first tap because it occurred outside the kill zone.",
    "Step 5: Once inside kill zone, price tagged the 0.79 with bodies still respecting the hourly FVG, then displaced lower, creating a 5-minute fair value gap.",
    "Step 6: Dropped to the 1-minute chart and identified a full-bodied 1-minute candle reaching into the 5-minute FVG and displacing lower, forming an order block entry.",
    "Step 7: Set entry at the 1-minute order block with stop above the high of the order block, targeting prior session / London session lows for approximately a 3R trade."
  ],
  "outcome": "Approximately 3R short trade reaching prior session/London session lows.",
  "lessons": "Top-down execution: use the HTF OTE/FVG confluence to define the POI, wait for kill zone timing, then drop down to LTF for a precision entry via displacement and order block — combining HTF bias, timing, and LTF confirmation yields high R:R trades.",
